The paper deals with the problem of accurate estimation of the position of network nodes, which is a common problem in wireless networks and mobile computing. The paper proposes a new distributed recursive position estimator that combines information from multiple and heterogeneous sensor measurements. This suggests that the paper could belong to the sub-categories of Information Theory (cs.IT), Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI), Systems and Control (cs.SY), Robotics (cs.RO), and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). Among these, cs.IT and cs.NI are the most likely categories as they deal with the fundamental limits of information processing and communication in networks, which is the focus of the paper. The other categories are also relevant as they deal with the design and control of mobile systems, which is an important aspect of the proposed estimator.
